ermine the cosmological constants,\n$\\Omega_m$ and $\\Omega_\\Lambda$ within 2$\\sigma$ confidence level. We present\nthe first steps in modelling of light curves for H$\\beta$ and MgII and discuss\nthe quasar selection in the context of photometric reverberation mapping with\nLarge Synoptic Survey Telescope (LSST). With the onset of the LSST era, we\nexpect a huge rise in the overall quasar counts and redshift range covered\n($z\\lesssim 7.0$), which will provide a better constraint of AGN properties\nwith cosmological purposes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 12 Sep 2019 11:25:39 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 3 Dec 2019 19:00:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-12-05"}
